Package etomica.species

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ISpecies
    An ISpecies holds information about how to construct a molecule, and creates molecules on demand.
    ISpeciesOriented  
    SpeciesAgentManager.AgentSource<E>
    Interface for an object that wants an agent associated with each AtomType in a Simulation.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Species
    Type for atom that is a group of other atoms, and for which its node is an instance of AtomTreeNodeGroup.
    SpeciesAgentManager<E>
    AtomTypeAgentManager acts on behalf of client classes (an AgentSource) to manage agents in every AtomType in a box.
    SpeciesOriented
    Atom type for a rigid molecule with an orientation and (therefore) a moment of inertia.
    SpeciesPolyhedron
    Species in which molecules are made of a single atom of type SpheroPolyhedron
    SpeciesSpheres
    Species in which molecules are made of arbitrary number of spheres, with each sphere having the same mass and size (same type).
    SpeciesSpheresCustom
    Species in which molecules are made of arbitrary number of spheres, each of a specified type.
    SpeciesSpheresHetero
    Species in which molecules are made of arbitrary number of atoms, with each atom have a given atom type.
    SpeciesSpheresMono
    Species in which molecules are each made of a single spherical atom.
    SpeciesSpheresRotating
    Species in which molecules are made of a single atom of type OrientedSphere
    SpeciesSpheresRotatingMolecule
    Species in which molecules are made of a single atom.
